# TimChat frontend

## Architecture

Frontend строится feature-oriented на Angular.

```
src/app
  ├─ core
  │   ├─ auth
  │   ├─ api
  │   ├─ realtime
  │   ├─ routing
  │   └─ layout
  ├─ shared
  │   ├─ ui
  │   ├─ util
  │   └─ models
  ├─ features
  │   ├─ auth
  │   ├─ workspace
  │   ├─ channels
  │   ├─ chat
  │   ├─ call
  │   ├─ presence
  │   ├─ profile
  │   └─ settings
  └─ app.routes.ts
```

## Key services / stores

- `AuthStore` — auth state
- `WorkspaceStore` — workspace context
- `ChannelStore` — channels
- `ChatStore` — chat messages
- `PresenceStore` — live presence
- `CallStore` — call state
- `RealtimeGateway` — WebSocket connection management
- `RtcMediaService` — WebRTC media
- `DeviceService` — device management
- `AttachmentUploadService` — file uploads

## Frontend role

Frontend orchestrates UX and media lifecycle, но не владеет authoritative business state.
Авторитетное состояние определяется сервером.
Frontend отображает то, что сервер объявил effective state.

## UI direction

Cursor-inspired design language:
- light-theme-first
- minimalistic
- dense
- professional
- desktop-first
- editor-like

Цель — high-quality operational workspace:
compact controls, clean typography, subtle borders, strong layout hierarchy, contextual side panels, low visual noise.

Продукт должен выглядеть как серьёзный рабочий инструмент для ежедневной коммуникации, а не как декоративный dashboard или маркетинговый мессенджер.

## Layout zones

- **left navigation rail** — workspace switching
- **secondary sidebar** — channels / sections / threads
- **main central area** — chat timeline or active room content
- **right contextual panel** — members, presence, moderation, audit, pinned items, call details
- **compact top bar** — current context, search, quick actions

## UX priorities

- fast scanning
- high information density
- predictable interaction zones
- keyboard-friendly workflows
- low-noise state presentation
- clear distinction between stable context and live-changing context

## Anti-patterns

Не делай:
- oversized cards
- excessive whitespace
- decorative gradients
- mobile-first dashboard composition
- marketing-style decorative UI
